  "text": "In a pertinent study by [CITATION_1] which examined the extent to which employees managed chronic illnesses, and whether they disclosed such illnesses in their workplace, questionnaires were sent to all 5,000 employees of a university in the United Kingdom. Employees were asked to report if they had a chronic illness, specifically; depression and anxiety, arthritis, diabetes, musculoskeletal pain, migraine, heart disease, irritable bowel disease and any other non-listed chronic illness, and to specify measures taken in relation to self-management of their illness and whether they disclosed their illness in the workplace. The study had a response rate of 44 % or 2,200 completed questionnaires, of which 34 % of respondents, or 748 employees, reported having at least one chronic health condition.",
